              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18367790434978864680">To the author: Thank you so much for a free copy of your novel! It was enjoyable, inspirational and educational! Also, congratulations to you on your novel! I have no doubt you will be successful with your writing. :)<br/><br/>My review (rating 5 stars-I would give more stars if I could): --------&gt; This was a good book written by a good first time author. This novel was different from anything that I have read before, it was very original. It has good quality too. The editing was some of the best that I h</span>
  <span id="freeText18367790434978864680" style="display:none">To the author: Thank you so much for a free copy of your novel! It was enjoyable, inspirational and educational! Also, congratulations to you on your novel! I have no doubt you will be successful with your writing. :)<br /><br />My review (rating 5 stars-I would give more stars if I could): --------&gt; This was a good book written by a good first time author. This novel was different from anything that I have read before, it was very original. It has good quality too. The editing was some of the best that I have seen in a first time author. I was very surprised this was Mrs. Acajou's first book. She wrote it as if she has written many books before this one. It was full of content and wisdom too. If you like to learn a little while reading, please read this novel.<br /><br /> I knew within the first few sentences that I would like this novel. There are so many good things about this book. I read it almost as if I were reading something important like the bible. The message was good and strong (I even saw a few biblical scriptures included). It was not something to be read lightly or just for entertainment. This was something to read to learn and understand more about your life. It is about having the right thoughts (positive thoughts), love, life, hope, forgiveness, acceptance, etc. I even saw discontentment, hate, resentment and other characters within the book. All of these elements came together to show how we have power over our lives. We may not have power over the things that have already happened but, we can have power over how we react to them and what we do in the future. <br /><br />I do not want to spoil anything for whomever may read it. There were some parts where I cried a little, and I laughed some too. I read and re-read parts. I took notes on some parts too. I love books where you really learn something new or where you are reminded of something to help you in your life. This was one of those books. It took me about three months or so to read this because my life got a little busier than usual and I did not want to rush through just to say I that finished it quickly. The message felt so important to me. It blessed my life, I still feel the effects of it when it comes to thinking more positively. It is helping me to pay more attention to my thoughts for sure. I try to drive away the negative ones as soon as they come because I want my life to be as positive as possible. I did not know that I needed to read this, but I did. I will re-read this book just like I re-read the bible and other spiritual material. I thank the author for writing this and for bringing it into my life right on time. Page 127 was one of my favorite pages. It speaks about love, the true meaning of love.<br /><br />I also loved the way the book started. Book two started off well also. The whole thing was good. It was longer than most books I read but, it was worth it. Most times I tend to read shorter stories because I don't have as much time to read as I would like.<br /><br />If you are a person who cries easily when something touches your heart, please read this with tissues nearby. I cried through some of this as if I were in church or at a good therapy session. It was that good. If you think you want to read this, please try it for yourself. I hope you like it as much as I did. Please do not overlook this new author. Writing is definitely one of her gifts. I'm a fan. In the words of Tamar Braxton (Yes, I am also a Braxton fan, lol.), "SHE DID THAT!!!" Mrs. Acajou did a great job with this novel! I can't say it enough! Another reviewer said that they could see this book as a movie, I agree. She wrote well enough for the events to be visualized easily. <br /><br />*I received a copy of this book for free in exchange for an honest review. I was not paid for my rating or review.* Also, I do not give a good review or rating just because I was given a free book. I rate books on how much I like them and connect with them. * Last but not least, thank you so much to Lyra Jade Acajou for a free copy of your novel!!! I feel honored and blessed for the chance to read it. It is truly unlike anything that I have read!</span>
  <a data-text-id="18367790434978864680" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

